				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Oh please, don't get me wrong. I have nothing against Verant, just the attitude of the current GM's..<BR>
<BR>
I used to date one, he was a Server GM.. but I won't go into details about who he is or what Server he worked with... besides, we broke up five months ago and haven't talked since.<BR>
<BR>
But I know how Verant works... they have gotten the game world so big (and it will get bigger in the coming years) that the actual Game Master's themselves spend more time trouble shooting and such stuff that Verant hired a special team of Game Master's to run Events...<BR>
<BR>
They do nothing but sit in a room all day and plan out Events to do on the various Server's then go out and do them every week or so, often it is just some dumb little event that never gets any mention on sites like Everlore, but other times it is a big Event that does get mentioned.<BR>
<BR>
They do have a preferrence of which Server gets which type of Event too, because they know their player communities...<BR>
<BR>
On one Server they will just do an Event with some story line to get players involved, while an another Server they do an Event where they themselves are just having their own personal fun and just killing us Players for the heck of it. <BR>
<BR>
But then we go and complaign, and a Game Master tells us in a petition, &quot;It's just an Event, have fun and enjoy it...&quot; Or, like they have said a few times on my Server, &quot;This isn't the &quot;normal&quot; type of event your used too.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Now... as for my earlier post, sorry of it came out a little too harshly, I do tend to harbor ill wishes towards them, though not all are like the one I dated... we were engaged, but last Christmas, after Luclin was released, he told me that his job and the game was more important...<BR>
<BR>
So I left him.
